lf.long: Thin trunks rise with wide gaps between them. Dull light falls across dry needles and scattered brush.

p.long: A flat plain stretches out in every direction. Wind presses through short grass.

f.long: Trees gather close, their limbs tangled above the ground. The understory is thin and uneven.

df.long: Dense growth closes in on all sides. The canopy blocks most of the light.

w.long: Dark water spreads without clear edge. Low ripples drift across the surface.

d.long: Pale sand runs out in hard waves. The air hangs dry and still.

h.long: Low hills roll in soft, broken lines. Stone shows through thin soil.

m.long: Wet ground shifts beneath a cover of reeds. Shallow pools gleam between mud and grass.

s.long: Dark water sits between heavy growth. Rotting trunks lean over the still surface.

b.long: Bare earth stretches out with little sign of growth. Scattered stones lie exposed to the wind.

default.long: The land here is quiet and open. No clear paths remain.
